sentences: Hieronymus Payer (13 February 1787 in Vienna-Meidling; died 17 August 1845 in the same place) was an Austrian composer and pianist.
Hieronymus Payer (13 February 1787 in Vienna-Meidling; died 17 August 1845 in the same place) was an Austrian composer and pianist.
In 1806 he became a conductor in the so-called Meidlinger Summer Theatre, for which he even wrote some small Singspiels.
In 1806 he became a conductor in the so-called Meidlinger Summer Theatre, for which he even wrote some small Singspiels.
Payer introduced in 1821 in Vienna for the first time the Physharmonica in a public concert.
Three years later he became a conductor in Amsterdam (at the Hoogduitse Schouwburg) and in 1825, in Paris.
